result.execSummary:
The defendant Angel Sanchez-Cervantes was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: DA Gerald Fox appeared for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Sebion.  Interpreter E.S. sworn.  Defendant plead no contest to count 2 and 4.  Counts 1 and 3 dismissed, but read in for sentencing purposes.  .  Court recited the charges and possible penalties of the counts he plead to.  Court confirmed prior OWI conviction.  Citizenship warnings given.  He understood.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  Defendant understood.  Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the pleas.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the pleas.  Found guilty of counts 2 and 4.  State recommended 2 years probation.  Concurrent.  Count 2, Act 100.  $1505.00.  15 days jail, all but the first 5 days stayed.  EMP ok.  Revoke DL 12 mo and IID.  Count 4.  6 months jail.  EMP ok.  Concurrent to count 2.  Attorney Sebion agrees with State's recommendation,  but less jail on count 4.  30-60 days.  Defendant did not exercise his right to allocution.  Court ordered:  sentence withheld, 2 years probation concurrent.   Count 2, Act 100 probation.  $1505.00.  To be paid monthly through probation.  Pay in full during the term of probation.  15 days jail, all but the first 5 days stayed.  Start 3/1 by noon.   EMP allowed, according to jail rules.  Alc. assmt and DSP.    Revoke DL 12 mo and IID.  Count 4.  60 days jail.  Start by 3/1 by noon.  EMP allowed according to jail rules.     The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.    Not to enter into any bars, taverns, liquor stores, liquor department of grocery stores, the bar areas of restaurants. Defendant may not possess or consume any alcohol, nor be anywhere alcohol is available for consumption on the premises where the defendant is located.  CC.
